Text.Value: What was that? I feel strange... clear.
*The only paw prints you can see belong to the beast itself - it has neither mate nor litter.*
I doubt he loves you back.
Check the ground for signs of other paw prints.
Something doesn't seem quite right - take a closer look.
The only liar here is your 'master'. Let's end him together.
Bold words, prey. But I kill who I please.
Master is most generous with his meat-gifts. The rot is only skin-shallow. The kicks he gives, most earned.
*The beast purrs as it enjoys your touch...*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The Player scritches the Displacer Beast behind its ears, which the beast enjoys.

Text.Value: *The creature eyes you with vague interest...*

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Though the beast enjoys a good flirt, it's toying with you - it finds you unconvincing and unappealing.

Text.Value: Go away!
I need no sign. My belly is full, my spirit fed. Your words are not wanted here.
*...But only for a moment - it's not your affection it craves.*

EditorData.AnimationTags: [Beast] Retreats from players touch, pulls attention away. <ChrisW>
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The beast haughtily turns its attention away from the player.
EditorData.SFXTags: [KB] Displayer Growl - snapping out of it's bliss

Text.Value: *Try as you might, you can't seem to meet the beast's eyes.*

EditorData.AnimationTags: [Player] looks intently, trying different angles to see properly. <ChrisW>
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The displacement effect of the beast prevents the player from making eye contact.

Text.Value: *A few merregons and an orthon - could the beast really be infatuated with one of these creatures?*
*The back of your eye tingles - there's magic in the beast's gut.*
GO AWAY.
You lie. Your breath stinks of double-speak.
*It's a displacer beast - alone, and tame.*
*Growl.*
Slave? You dare call master's heart-jewel a slave?
*You see nothing nearby that might appeal to a displacer beast's desires.*
I'll not start the fight but I'll help you end it.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Beginning to reckon with the truth, the beast begins to turn toward anger - though it can't get over its amorous feelings for the orthon. It's been charmed for too long.

Text.Value: Live and let love, I suppose.
*Growl.*
My claws itch, my blood burns.
Now let that silence stick.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: The displacer beast is not impressed. She finds you irritating.

Text.Value: *The beast stares at you.*
But it's ridiculous.
*Growl.*
Now LEAVE.
How does that even work?
Very much. Now get out of our territory.
Not just any orthon. Master is the darkest of desire. None compare to him.
You're in love with an orthon?
*Light seems to bend around the beast's body.*

EditorData.VFXTags: [KB] Light bending around the Displacer's body

Text.Value: *You smell sour milk and rot on its breath.*
I'm ready.
Leave. Before I get hungry again.
False master! Hind-legged liars, all! I'll shred you.
Attack.
Poor servant, poor poor servant. My master would never be so cruel.
The orthon sold you to me. I'm your master now.
I've a wounded pride. Leave me to nurse it.
Something doesn't seem quite right - take a closer look.
I was belly-hollow - close to death.
I'll be on my way.
Would he die for you, as you would for him?
*The beast eyes you with interest.*

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: The beast considers the player for its next meal.

Text.Value: You mock our heart-bond?
A poor word-kiss.
Make eye contact with the beast.

EditorData.logicalname: LOGIC - Player doesn't know about the poison

Text.Value: I am his love.
*You manage to contain yourself.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Player visibly stifles a laugh. (Emotion key, not animation)

Text.Value: *Though its posture is defensive, its eyes are soft - the beast is in love.*
Reconsider, challenger.
*...which quickly becomes a sneer.*
Look around to see who it might be in love with.
Reach out to stroke one of its tentacles.
Something doesn't seem quite right - take a closer look.
I know my tastes. And I'm not known for sharing.
I remember... quick flesh, hot blood.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: The beast is initially outraged, but your logic is infallible, and awakens thoughts and feelings it has buried for a long time with the help of the charm potion.

Text.Value: Stop your mewling before I shred you.
His what now?
That's between me and master. Go sniff elsewhere, prey.
Disease? No. Love is a birthright. I pity the beast who is deprived.
You're kidding, right?
*This creature has been eating charmed spider meat.*
I have a servant who calls me Master, and his love disgusts me.
Stifle a laugh.
What master gives is my rightful due. Master is most kind.
I could ask you the same question.
*There's something off about this creature, but you can't tell what.*
I hope they chew him up in the Hells.
Leave.
You? But master loves me... master lied?

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: The beast is shocked - it has been blindly following its master out of love and adoration and now its illusion is shattered.

Text.Value: You're deluded.
What are you waiting for?
I don't answer to you, prey.
Master? Didn't think of your kind as slaves.
Give it a scratch behind the ears.
*The beast shudders - a moment of pleasure...*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The Player reaches out to stroke one of the beast's tentacles. The beast lets out a shudder of pleasure.

Text.Value: What business do you have in my master's den?
Shame to let a meal walk free...

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Like a cat taunting a mouse, its hunger and lust are palpable...

Text.Value: I am master's heart-chosen.
Something doesn't seem quite right - take a closer look.
Attack.
Enough interference! Let me be.
Why are you still in master's den?
You only love your master because he's been dosing this meat. He's manipulating you.
I love him. And he loves me.

EditorData.NodeContext: grasping for something it knows to be true

Text.Value: Master found me, fed me, then I... I...

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The beast looks confused - it appears to have forgotten how its story ends.
EditorData.InternalNodeContext: The beast can't (or won't) remember being charmed.

Text.Value: Leave.
You should consider me - I'm much better than him.
*There are too many prints - you cannot tell them apart.*
This is love. I am sure.
*Hiss.*
Imbecile. I shall make dust of your bones.
*Hiss.*
...But you don't appeal to my tastes.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: ... Until it becomes apparent that it's toying with you.

Text.Value: *You try to hold it in, but that only makes it worse.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Player visibly attempting to stifle a laugh. The displacer beast is furious.

Text.Value: Love is a disease like any other.
There's truth in you, stranger.
Before master, my prey was alive.
*Hiss.*
*...Before it retreats out of reach.*

EditorData.AnimationTags: *DUPE* [Beast] Retreats from players touch, pulls attention away. <ChrisW>
EditorData.InternalNodeContext: The beast is guilty - by enjoying your touch, it feels like it's betraying its master.
EditorData.SFXTags: [KB] Displayer Growl - snapping out of it's bliss

Text.Value: It's vulnerable - an opportunity. Attack.

Synopsis: Appears if the player tries to speak to the Displacer Beast. The player can learn that the beast is in love with the Orthon, and if they know that it has been charmed by him, they can attempt to convince it to join them in battle against the Orthon.
